Verses.Text:
 So I will block your way with a hedge of thorns;
And I will raise up a stone wall against her,
So that she cannot find her paths.

 I will engage myself to you forever;
And I will engage myself to you in righteousness and in justice,
In loyal love and in mercy.

 ‘In that day I will answer,’ declares Jehovah,
‘I will answer the heavens,
And they will answer the earth;

 It will be the same for the people as for the priest;
I will call them to account for their ways,
And I will bring on them the consequences of their actions.

 Their dealings do not permit them to return to their God,
Because there is a spirit of prostitution among them;
And Jehovah they do not acknowledge.

 The pride of Israel has testified against him;
Both Israel and Eʹphraim have stumbled in their error,
And Judah has stumbled with them.

 That is why I will cut them down by means of the prophets;
I will kill them with the words of my mouth.
And the judgments on you will shine as the light.

 I have seen a horrible thing in the house of Israel.
There Eʹphraim practices prostitution;
Israel has defiled itself.

 But they do not say in their heart that I will remember all their wickedness.
Now their dealings are all around them;
They are right in front of my face.

 For they approach with hearts burning like an oven.
All night long the baker sleeps;
In the morning the oven blazes like a flaming fire.

 For this is from Israel.
A craftsman made it, and it is not God;
The calf of Samarʹia will be reduced to splinters.

 Although they hire them from among the nations,
I will now round them up;
They will begin to suffer because of the burden imposed by king and princes.

 They will not continue dwelling in the land of Jehovah;
Instead, Eʹphraim will return to Egypt,
And in Assyrʹia they will eat what is unclean.

 They will no longer pour out wine offerings to Jehovah;
Their sacrifices will not please him.
They are like the bread of mourning;
All those eating it will defile themselves.
For their bread is for themselves alone;
It will not come into the house of Jehovah.

 The watchman of Eʹphraim was with my God.
But now all the ways of his prophets are as the traps of a birdcatcher;
There is animosity in the house of his God.

 Even if they raise children,
I will bereave them until no man is left;
Yes, woe to them when I turn away from them!

 “Israel is a degenerate vine yielding its fruit.
The more his fruit increases, the more he multiplies his altars;
The better his land produces, the more splendid his sacred pillars.

 Their heart is hypocritical;
Now they will be found guilty.
There is one who will break their altars and destroy their pillars.

 With the ropes of men I kept drawing them, with the cords of love;
And I was to them like one lifting a yoke from their jaws,
And I gently brought food to each one.

 They will tremble like a bird when they come out of Egypt,
Like a dove out of the land of Assyrʹia;
And I will settle them in their houses,” declares Jehovah.

 Jehovah has a legal case against Judah;
He will call for an accounting against Jacob according to his ways,
And he will repay him according to his deeds.

 Eʹphraim keeps saying, ‘Indeed, I have become rich;
I have found wealth.
And in all my toil, they will not find anything wrong or sinful.’

 Jacob ran away to the territory of Aʹram;
Israel served there for a wife,
And for a wife he guarded sheep.

 Eʹphraim has caused bitter offense;
His bloodguilt remains on him;
His Lord will repay him for his reproach.”

 “When Eʹphraim spoke, there was trembling;
He was prominent in Israel.
But he became guilty with regard to Baʹal and died.

 But I am Jehovah your God from the land of Egypt;
You knew no God except me,
And besides me there is no savior.

 The pangs of childbirth will come for him.
But he is an unwise child;
He does not present himself when it is time to be born.

 I will become like the dew to Israel;
He will blossom like the lily
And will send down his roots like the trees of Lebʹanon.
